 Lady Frere - Police are on the heels of a suspect, who raped and attacked a 67-year-old woman and her son  at Tsembeyi Administrative Area on Tuesday night between 20HO0 and the early hours of Wednesday. "It is alleged that old woman was sleeping in her house and her son was sleeping  in another room when she heard someone breaking  the window and entering the house," police spokesperson, Captain Namhla Mdleleni said. "She was raped and stabbed." Capt Mdleleni said that during that process, victim's son entered in order to rescue his mother, but suspect also stabbed the son and afterwards ran away. "Police were summoned and on arrival, both victims were taken to hospital as they were both injured," she said. "A case of rape and attempted murder were opened and no arrest yet. "Police  are following the leads and appeal to anyone, who can assist them in arresting the perpetrator to please contact Detective Sgt Ndileka Bokolo  at 0798969645 or 0860010111." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 